    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential buffer overflow in HARQ rounds statistics handling\n\n### Summary\nThis PR addresses a potential buffer overflow issue in the handling of HARQ rounds statistics. The `rounds` arrays in `NR_bler_stats_t` and `NR_mac_dir_stats_t` have a fixed size of 8 elements, but the code was potentially accessing these arrays with indices that could exceed the array bounds when `harq_round_max` was set to a value greater than 8.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/main.c`: Added bounds checking in loops that iterate over the `rounds` array to ensure `i < 8`\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_dlsch.c`: Added assertion to check bounds before accessing `UE->mac_stats.dl.rounds[harq->round]`\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_RA.c`: Added assertion to check bounds before accessing `UE->mac_stats.dl.rounds[harq->round]`\n- `openair2/GNB_APP/gnb_config.c`: Added constraints to ensure `harq_round_max` doesn't exceed 8 when reading from configuration\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue can be reproduced by configuring `dl_harq_round_max` or `ul_harq_round_max` to a value greater than 8 in the gNB configuration. When the code attempts to access the `rounds` arrays with an index >= 8, it would result in a buffer overflow, potentially causing a segfault or memory corruption.\n\nWith these changes, the code now properly validates array indices before accessing the `rounds` arrays, preventing the buffer overflow.\n"
}